This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the effectiveness of a continuous active learning method for technology-assisted review, which involves retrieving and reviewing documents from a collection. It may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves natural language processing for relevance assessment. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for autonomous decision-making, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the reliability of the method, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
